🎬 Movie Recommendation System (Content-Based Filtering)
📌 Project Description

Developed a Movie Recommendation System that suggests similar movies to users based on content similarity. 
The system leverages machine learning techniques and vector similarity to provide personalized recommendations
using preprocessed datasets stored in movie.pkl and similarity.pkl.

🧠 Model & Approach

This project uses a Content-Based Filtering approach.

👉 Instead of using user behavior, the system recommends movies based on:

Genre
Keywords
Cast
Crew
Overview (movie description)
⚙️ How It Works
Data Preprocessing
Cleaned and merged movie metadata
Combined important features (genres, cast, etc.) into a single text column called tags
Applied text preprocessing:
Lowercasing
Removing spaces
Stemming
Feature Extraction
Used Bag of Words (CountVectorizer) to convert text into numerical vectors
Created a high-dimensional vector space representation of movies
Similarity Calculation
Applied Cosine Similarity to measure similarity between movie vectors
Stored the similarity matrix in similarity.pkl
Stored processed movie data in movie.pkl
🤖 Model Used
Model Type: Content-Based Recommendation Model
Algorithm:
CountVectorizer (for text vectorization)
Cosine Similarity (for similarity scoring)

👉 This is NOT a deep learning model, but a vector space model, widely used in real-world recommendation systems.

🔄 Recommendation Flow
User selects a movie
System retrieves its index from movie.pkl
Looks up similarity scores from similarity.pkl
Sorts movies based on similarity
Returns top 5 most similar movies
🧪 Example

👉 Input: "Avatar"
👉 Output: List of similar movies like:

Guardians of the Galaxy
John Carter
Star Trek
🛠️ Tech Stack
Python
Pandas, NumPy
Scikit-learn
Pickle (for model storage)
Streamlit (for UI, if used)
🚀 Key Features
Fast recommendations using precomputed similarity
Lightweight and efficient (no heavy model inference)
Easy to scale and deploy
Clean UI (if integrated with Streamlit)
📦 Files Used
movie.pkl → Contains processed movie dataset
similarity.pkl → Stores cosine similarity matrix
